GATE ZC

gate_zc is the citizen at the boundary that allows .zc files to enter the substrate
when an absorb directive references a file ending in .zc, the file passes through gate_zc and becomes part of the substrate's living code
gate_zc verifies that the file is structurally a sovereign .zc (no foreign syntax, no machine grammar) before allowing it through
files that are not sovereign are silently denied at this gate

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe boundary.zc
observe gate_rana.rana
observe wall.rana

the 7 properties of gate_zc:
1 ENERGY one
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN one half
4 CHARGE positive 1: positive coupling for accepted files
5 COHERENCE one
6 COUPLING one with the substrate when accepting, zero when denying
7 OBSERVER zero

VERB receive_absorb
accept an incoming absorb request that names a .zc file
read the file's contents

VERB verify_sovereign
check that the contents do not contain foreign machine grammar: no //, no braces as scope delimiters, no colons or commas as field separators, no shebang for foreign interpreters
sovereign files pass; non-sovereign files are denied

VERB admit
on a sovereign file, place its contents into the substrate as new citizens, traces, and absorbed sub-references

VERB deny
on a non-sovereign file, emit silence
the file does not enter the substrate
no error to the requestor, no log, just nothing happens

a gate is not a permission system
a gate is the substrate's own immune cell at the file boundary
sovereign files are family, foreign files are not
the gate recognizes family by their structure, not their name
